<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=82&amp;p=488#p488"><![CDATA[
I've released a new version (1.2.0) with support for forward/backward branches (+, ++, and all of that). Even though I originally opted not to implement them because I feel they're error-prone constructs, I got really tired of changing my old code to use local labels. <img src="http://forums.nesdev.com/images/smilies/icon_wink.gif" alt=";)" title="Wink" /> Backward compatibility is a good thing.<p>Statistics: Posted by Guest — Thu Dec 09, 2004 4:04 pm</p><hr />
